name: all-trans-phytoene synthase
classes: Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups;
Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups (only sub-subclass identified to date)
reaction: 2 geranylgeranyl diphosphate = all-trans-phytoene + 2 diphosphate (overall reaction) [RN:R07916]; (1a) 2 geranylgeranyl diphosphate = diphosphate + prephytoene diphosphate [RN:R02065]; (1b) prephytoene diphosphate = all-trans-phytoene + diphosphate [RN:R07270]
comment: Requires Mn2+ for activity. The enzyme from the bacterium Pantoea agglomerans (previously known as Erwinia herbicola) produces the all-trans isomer of phytoene. cf. EC 2.5.1.32, 15-cis-phytoene synthase.

references.title: The stereochemistry of trans-phytoene synthesis. Some observations on lycopersene as a carotene precursor and a mechanism for the synthesis of cis- and trans-phytoene.
Bacterial phytoene synthase: molecular cloning, expression, and characterization of Erwinia herbicola phytoene synthase.
